name: src/ella.js
content:
export {default as Vec2}        from "./Vec2.js";
export {default as Vec2Builder} from "./Vec2Builder.js";

name: src/Vec2.js
Vec2
description: A two dimensional vector.

params.name: x
params.description: The x-coordinate.

params.name: y
params.description: The y-coordinate.

name: x
description: The x-coordinate.

name: y
description: The y-coordinate.

name: add
description:
Adds another vector to this vector. The original vectors remain
unaffected.

params.name: v
params.description: The vector to be added.

name: sub
description:
Subtracts another vector from this vector. The original vectors remain
unaffected.

params.name: v
params.description: The vector to be subtracted.

name: mul
description:
Multiplies this vector by a scalar. The original vector remains
unaffected.

params.name: s
params.description: The scalar by which the vector gets multiplied.

return.description: The product of vector and scalar.

name: div
description: Divides this vector by a scalar. The original vector remains unaffected.

params.name: s
params.description: The scalar by which the vector gets divided.

return.description: The quotient of vector and scalar.

name: length
description: Calculates the length of the vector.

name: normalize
description:
Creates a vector that points in the same direction as the original vector
but has length 1. The original vector remains unaffected.

name: dot
description: Calculates the dot product of this vector and the given vector.

params.name: v
params.description: The second argument.

return.description: The dot product of the two vectors.

name: rotate
description:
Rotates this vector by the given angle. The original vector remains
unaffected.

params.name: alpha
params.description: The angle by which to rotate given in radians.

name: toString
description: Returns a textual representation of this vector.

return.description: A textual representation of this vector.

name: src/Vec2Builder.js
Vec2Builder
description:
A builder for a two dimensional vector. It can be use to perform vector
operations without allocating a lot of temporary objects. All calculations
are performed in place.

name: fromVec2
description: Makes a builder representing the given vector.

params.name: v
params.description: The vector to make a builder for.

params.name: x
params.description: The x-coordinate.

params.name: y
params.description: The y-coordinate.

name: x
description: The x-coordinate.

name: y
description: The y-coordinate.

name: add
description: Adds another vector to this one.

params.name: x
params.description: The x coordinate of the vector to add.

params.name: y
params.description: The y coordinate of the vector to add.

name: sub
description: Subtracts another vector from this one.

params.name: x
params.description: The x coordinate of the vector to subtract.

params.name: y
params.description: The y coordinate of the vector to subtract.

name: mul
description: Multiplies this vector with a scalar.

params.name: s
params.description: The scalar to multiply with.

name: div
description: Divides this vector by a scalar.

params.name: s
params.description: The scalar to divide by.

name: length
description: Calculates the length of this vector.

name: normalize
description: Sets the length of this vector to 1 while keeping its direction.

name: dot
description: Calculates the dot product of this vector and the given one.

params.name: x
params.description: The x coordinate of the other vector.

params.name: y
params.description: The y coordinate of the other vector.

return.description: The dot product of the two vectors.

name: rotate
description: Rotates this vector by the given angle.

params.name: alpha
params.description: The angle by which to rotate given in radians.

name: toVec2
description: Returns the vector this builder represents.

return.description: The vector represented by this builder.

name: toString
description: Returns a textual representation of this vector.

return.description: A textual representation of this vector.
